<hr>
<details>
    <summary class="r-margin clickable h3 normal">line</summary>
    <pre><code>{{{example-1}}}</code></pre>
</details>
<p>Groups units on one horizontal line. Note: for mobile layout units may be stacked to avoid horizontal scrolling.</p>
<hr>

<details>
    <summary class="r-margin clickable h3 normal">unit</summary>
    <pre><code>{{{example-2}}}</code></pre>
</details>
<p>Base class which divides a line into sections (columns).</p>
<hr>

<details>
    <summary class="r-margin clickable h3 normal">r-sizeXofY</summary>
    <pre><code>{{{example-3-1}}}</code></pre>
</details>
<p>Extends <code>unit</code>. Indicates the number of grid units this element spans, for example <code>r-size2of3</code>
    would take up 2 of 3 columns. Collapses to 1 column at 768px.</p>

<p class="strong">Intended use: Main layout grid!</p>
<hr>

<details>
    <summary class="r-margin clickable h3 normal">sizeXofY</summary>
    <pre><code>{{{example-3-2}}}</code></pre>

    <p>Supported fractions:</p>
    <ul class="bullets pll">
        <li>1</li>
        <li>1/2</li>
        <li>1/3</li>
        <li>2/3</li>
        <li>1/4</li>
        <li>3/4</li>
        <li>1/5</li>
        <li>2/5</li>
        <li>3/5</li>
        <li>4/5</li>
        <li>1/6</li>
        <li>5/6</li>
    </ul>
</details>
<p>Extends <code>unit</code>. Indicates the fractional width of the unit, for example <code>size3of4</code> would take
    up three quarters, or 75%, of the horizontal space.</p>
<p class="strong">
    Intended use: Non-responsive liquid elements
</p>
<hr>

