<p>Extends <code>line</code>. Responsive column setup for content. Classname indicates number of colums, for example
    <code>r-cols2to4</code> will fit 2 columns on mobile screens and 4 columns from 768px and up.</p>

<p class="strong">Intended use: Column based contents</p>
<!-- ** -->
<hr>

<details>
    <summary class="r-margin clickable h3 normal">colsXupto[Breakpoint]</summary>
    <pre><code>{{{example-6}}}</code></pre>
    <p>Supported column count: 1 - 8</p>
    <p>Supported breakpoints:</p>
    <ul class="bullets pll">
        <li>480</li>
        <li>640</li>
        <li>768</li>
        <li>990</li>
    </ul>
</details>

<p>Extends <code>line</code>.
<p><code>.cols[X]upto[breakpoint]</code> Sets number of columns up to specified breakpoint</p>
<p><code>.cols[X]from990</code> Sets number of columns from 990 and up</p>

<p>Classname indicates number of colums at specific breakpoints, for example
    <code>.cols1upto480 .cols2upto768 .cols4from990</code> will fit 1 column below 480px, 2 columns between 480px and 767px, and 4 columns from 990px to infinity</p>
    <p class="red">! Works in conjunction with colsXfrom990, remember to set this aswell, or 990px+ will get whatever is default (usually 1col )</p>

<p class="strong">Intended use: Column based contents where we need more control</p>
